Ethel Rider, 87, fell from her bed at the Half Acre Care Home in Radcliffe, Manchester .
Carers Susan Logan and Lauren Gillies, 25, lied about what had happened .
Logan, 59, tried to turn her by herself - but she was hoisted back into bed .
She was left 'cowering' in pain after falling from bed for 40 minutes .
Judge branded carers 'idle' and said they had cut corners to give themselves longer breaks .